02/03/2005
SKOPJE, Macedonia -- NATO's Assistant Secretary General for Political Issues, Guenter Altenburg, is moderately optimistic about Macedonia's bid to obtain membership in the Pact. 
He met with Foreign Minister Ilinka Mitreva on Tuesday (1 March), as part of an ongoing NATO inspection mission to the country. 
According to Altenburg, the reform process is generally going well, though decisive steps are needed to restructure the judicial sector, boost the economy and combat corruption.
In other news, Montenegrin President Filip Vujanovic kicks off a two-day visit to Macedonia on Wednesday, at the invitation of counterpart Branko Crvenkovski. 
Talks are expected to focus on strengthening economic and trade ties. 
(Makfax, A1 TV - 02/03/05; A1 TV, Makfax - 01/03/05)
